<p><code>as.Date()</code> has a useful function in that it can give you the last <code>n</code> days as, e.g.:</p>  <pre><code>dt &lt;- Sys.Date()-6 &gt; dt  [1] "2015-09-25" </code></pre>  <p>Is there a way to tell it to give the last six months instead of the last six days?</p>  <p>I need something more precise than <code>6*30</code>, as it should be the last day of the month.</p>